properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 1 at 9:43AM EST until February 2 at 5:00PM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...West to southwest winds 15 to 25 knots today becoming
northwest 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt tonight into Sunday.
Seas building to 5 to 8 feet by tonight into Sunday.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Deerfield Beach to Ocean Reef FL
out 20 NM, Coastal waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield
Beach FL out 20 NM, Waters from Deerfield Beach to Ocean Reef
FL from 20 to 60 NM excluding the territorial waters of
Bahamas and Waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach FL
from 20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...Until 5 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should use caution when
entering or exiting the inlets and jetty areas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM EST SUNDAY
